column2: Mostly sunny with a slight breeze.
This is the last reading for 1986.
Partly cloudy and wind at 0-5 mph.
Clear and there is a 5 mph wind.
Partly cloudy- wind 5-10 miles per hour.
Partly cloudy- 10-15 mph wind- lot of boat traffic.
Clear- 5-15 mph- 6.3" of rain in September (2.47" on 9/22).
Partly cloudy- wind 0-5 mph.- last reading
Thin overcast- hazy sun- E wind 0-5 mph
Sunny; wind SE at 5-8 mph; pine pollen on surface.
Clear; sunny; gentle breeze; no harvesting.
Mostly cloudy; south wind at 5-10 mph; weed harvester not working on lake.
Partly cloudy; wind NE 0-5 pH; weed cutting at east end of D.
The sky is clear and the wind is less than 5 mph.
Mostly sunny- and southwest wind at less than 5 mph.
Partly sunny- south wind less than 5 mph- about 3.7" of rain on July 11 and 12.
Clear- easterly wind less than 5 mph- about 0.5" of rain on July 22.
Thin overcast and a west wind less than 5 mph.
Clear sky and northwest wind at less than 5 mph.
Partly to mostly cloudy- southeast wind less than 5 mph- about 0.95" of rain on 8/12/92.
Partly cloudy and a southwest wind at about 5 mph.
Partly sunny- w-northwest wind about 5 mph.
Mostly cloudy- southerly wind at 0-5 mph- lake level about 3" below high water marker at dam.
Sunny- SE wind at 0-5 mph- more than 6" of rain in last two weeks.  This is last report for 1992.
Same comments as in Site A.
Clear- wind NE  less than 5 mph.
Clear- wind NW  less than 5 mph.
Clear- wind NE  greater than 5 mph.
Partly sunny.  Wind SW  less than 5 mph.
S-southwest wind- sky is clear- wind is about 5 mph.
Clear- wind about 5 mph from the west.
There was a lot of boating activity on the lake over the weekend- there was some floating wads on the surface.
Thin- hazy cloud cover.  Near calm.
Partly cloudy- wind W 0-5 mph.  1.50" of rain on 3 August
Partly cloudy- wind W about 5 mph.
Partly cloudy- wind is S  less than 5 mph
Mostly cloudy- wind NW  greater than 5 mph.
Partly cloudy- calm.  Last report for 1994.
Cloudy- wind is east 5-10mph.  Rain on 5/8 and 5/9 totaled 1.3"
Mostly cloudy- wind E 0-5 mph.  Our dam repair project is scheduled to start about 1 august.
Clear- hot- calm.  Clumps of algae on the surface.  Lake level will be lowered one foot to low watermark about August 1 when the dam will be repaired.  This will take 8-10 weeks.
Clear- hazy sunshine.  Wind N-Northwest 5+ mph.
Clear skies- wind SW at 0-5 mph.  Hot. dam repair starts on or about 14 August 1995.
Partly cloudy- wind is SW 0-5 mph.
Partly cloudy- wind SE 0-5 mph.  Lake will be lowered 1' in a week or so for dam repair.
Partly sunny- wind is SE about 5 mph- samples were taken a week to 10 days earlier this month because the lake level will be dropped one foot for 8 weeks during the Mt. Morris dam repair project.

Public perception also due to low water levels and lots of rain.  Clear- wind 5-10 mph.  Dam repair started 8/14.  Water level at low water mark.  About 9.7" of rain since 8/1 about 6.2" since 8/ ( ) .
Clear sky- wind 0-3 mph from west.
Clear sky- little or no wind. humid + hazy.
Cool day- about 50 degrees- sunny- wind NE @ 5 mph.
Sunny- wind south less than 5 mph- 2 " rain on 6/19- 1.75 " on 6/21.
Partly cloudy- gentle east breeze- .50" of rain in the morning.
Sunny and calm- 3.6 inches of rain on July 16th.
Partly cloudy variable breezes  2.8" rain on 6/11/98.
Partly cloudy NE wind 5 mph.  1.35" rain on 8/17/98. weed cutter working.
Clear NW wind 5 mph.  0.8" rain on 8/22/98.
Hazy sunshine and easterly wind less than five mph.
Sunny and easterly wind at less than five mph.
Partly cloudy and gentle westerly breeze.
Hazy sun and south wind at less than five mph.
Partly cloudy- S breeze- 1.8" rain on 7/8/99
Overcast- hazy sun- near calm.  3.4" rain on 7/18/99-7/19/99.
Sunny- calm- 9.56" rain so far in July.
Overcast- hazy sunshine- 40 F air temp- this is the last report for Morris Lake in 1999.
Overcast- north wind- too windy on 6/27 to take secchi readings.
Warm- humid- hazy sunshine- SW breeze.
Sunny and west wind at 0-5 mph.
Clear- wind westerly at 5 mph- and the air temperature is 40 degrees.
Ice out on Site D on 12 April 2002. Hazy day- partly cloudy- light easterly breeze.
Cloudy- near calm. Ice out on this site on 12 Apr
Partly cloudy- east breeze. Algae present.
Sample taken with Andy Hudak WI DNR while being trained to take water samples.
Judy Foster - Helper. Extremely hot. No measureable rainfall since 06/20/2012
Helper - Judy Foster - Hot + dry - No measureable rain since 6/20/2012
Judy Foster - Helper - Some drought relief - About .6" rain since 7/14.
Judy Foster - Helper       Julia + Trevor Foster (Grandchildren) - Helpers
Judy Foster - Helper.......This will be our last reading for 2012
Water still has a brackish appearance from spring run-off.Assisted by Judy Foster
Assisted by Judy Foster - Partly cloudy- but bright.
Assisted by Judy Foster Beautiful- cool sunny day
Assisted by Judy Foster Assisted by Judy Foster
Beautiful- sunny fall day. Slight southerly breeze. Assister by Judy Foster
Assited by Judy Foster. Another beautiful fall day! The water is calm. We saw a bald eagle soaring over the lake. This is the final reading for this season. See you in the spring!
Assisted by Judy Foster. Water is very brackish.
Assisted by Judy Foster. Lake still very brackish. Heavy rain on 6/1/2014 2.6"

Assisted by Judy Foster. Water is starting to clear- but still very brackish. Water appears to have a lot of suspended particulate in it. Last week the presence of Zebra Mussels was confirmed in Lake Morris by the DNR.
Assisted by Judy Foster. Water in Lakes C+D still brackish.
Assisted by Judy Foster. Zebra Mussel monitoring plates installed July 26- 2014 on my pier by Golden Sands R+D
Assisted by Judy Foster - Lake D appears very brown due to heavy runoff from June storms. Has not cleared.
Assisted by Judy Foster Assisted by Judy Foster Assisted by Judy Foster
Water still murky brown from spring run off.
Water dark brown due to run-off from heavy rains 6/15 to 6/17 2018. Total 6 inches of rainfall. Water dark brown due to run-off from heavy rains 6/15 to 6/17 2018. Total 6 inches of rainfall.
Nicest the water has looked all season!!
Water color is dark brown due to heavy rains (9.5 inches) from 8/25/18 to 9/3/18. Water clarity greatly reduced. Perception number is listed as N/A due to water color.

Water color is deep brown due to 9.5" rain from 8/25/18 to 9/3/18. Perception number based on water color- not algae content. Water clarity greatly reduced. Water color is dark brown due to heavy rains (9.5 inches) from 8/25/18 to 9/3/18. Water clarity greatly reduced. Perception number is listed as N/A due to water color.
Lake D - Deep Hole - Water in this location is still very brown and murky from heavy spring rains.
Day was partly cloudy- Westerly wind at 5-10 mph.
East wind- 5 mph- pc with hazy overcast.
Wind WSW 7- cloudy Wind WSW 7- cloudy
